snippet.textDisplay: It's a goalpariya/Rajbongshi folk song popularized by late padmashree Pratima Barua pandey. Also known as bhawaiya in North Bengal. Bengali has been imposed in that original composition as it sounds similar but tbh I feel sad that there's no were any mention or credits of goalpariya/ Rajbongshi folk  in the description. We live in peace and harmony with other cultures but at times they fail to even give us a proper credit. Our Koch Rajbongshi culture might just get left behind and lost in history (that's what haunts me)(ps- I love bengali songs but this isn't)
snippet.textOriginal: It's a goalpariya/Rajbongshi folk song popularized by late padmashree Pratima Barua pandey. Also known as bhawaiya in North Bengal. snippet.textDisplay: Maybe this is propagating Bengali folk among a whole different demographic! That way this serves a great purpose. But the spirit of this song is COMPLETELY lost in this rendition and arrangements. The rhythm is skewed and conflicting chords...Would be wonderful is some of the original song’s integrity and ambiance was even maintained a slight bit! 👎🏼
